data.description:

  • Fourth Quarter 2025 Guidance

    • Revenue is expected to be in the range of $192.7 million to $194.7 million, representing 13% to 14% year-over-year growth.
    • Net income per diluted share is expected to be in the range of $0.53 to $0.57, with fully diluted weighted average shares outstanding of 38.3 million shares.
    • Non-GAAP income per diluted share is expected to be in the range of $0.98 to $1.02.

    • Revenue is expected to be in the range of $751.6 million to $753.6 million, representing 18% growth over 2024.

    • Non-GAAP income per diluted share is expected to be in the range of $4.10 to $4.15.
    • Adjusted EBITDA is expected to be in the range of $229.7 million to $231.7 million, representing 23% to 24% growth over 2024.
    • Non-cash, share-based compensation expense is expected to be $58.3 million, depreciation expense is expected to be $21.1 million, and amortization expense is expected to be $37.1 million.
  • Shares -9.52% AH.

data.title: Arrow Electronics Non-GAAP EPS of $2.41 beats by $0.12, revenue of $7.71B beats by $40M
data.description:
• Arrow Electronics press release (ARW): Q3 Non-GAAP EPS of $2.41 beats by $0.12.
  • Revenue of $7.71B (+13.0% Y/Y) beats by $40M.

  • Fourth-Quarter 2025 Outlook

    • Consolidated sales of $7.80 billion to $8.40 billion vs $8.33B consensus, with global components sales of $5.10 billion to $5.50 billion, and global enterprise computing solutions sales of $2.70 billion to $2.90 billion

  • Shares -1%.

data.title: Roku stock slides after mixed Q3 report, tepid forecast
data.description:
Roku (ROKU) shares fell in post-market trading on Thursday after the company reported a mixed third quarter and provided a forecast that did not fulfill Wall Street's expectations.

Shares fell more than 15% in immediate reaction to the report before paring losses and are currently down more than 7%.

For the fourth quarter, Roku expects revenue to be $1.35B, slightly ahead of the Bloomberg consensus estimate of $1.32B; gross profit of $575M, a little above the $571.9M estimate; and adjusted EBITDA of $395M vs. the consensus estimate of $376.2M.

The company, which makes streaming devices and owns a complimentary, ad-supported channel, said users streamed 36.5B hours in Q3, up 15% from last year, but below the estimate of 37.5B hours. 

Net income for the three months ended September 30 was $28.8M, compared with a loss of $9M for the same period last year.

On a per-share basis, the company earned 16 cents, beating the average analyst expectation of 8 cents a share.

Revenue rose 14% to $1.21B and was in line with the consensus estimate.
